parties.raw_snippet:
THIS AGREEMENT (this “Agreement”), dated December 30, 2016 (the “Effective Date”), is
BETWEEN:
Paratek Pharmaceuticals, Inc., a company having a place of business at 75 Park Plaza, 4th Floor, Boston, MA 02116, USA (“Customer”)
AND:
CARBOGEN AMCIS AG, a company having a place of business at Hauptstrasse 171, CH 4416 Bubendorf, Switzerland (“Supplier” and, collectively
with Customer, the “Parties”, and each, a “Party).
parties.reasoning: The document explicitly lists the contracting parties in the "BETWEEN:" section immediately following the agreement heading and defines each by name and role (Customer and Supplier). These are the principal parties to the contract.

Date

contract_type.reasoning: The header/title of the document labels it an "Outsourcing Agreement" and the substantive obligations throughout the agreement require Supplier to Manufacture and supply the Product to Customer (manufacturing/supply of APIs), consistent with an outsourcing of manufacturing services. Thus the primary purpose is outsourcing/manufacturing/supply of product.

agreement_date.raw_snippet: THIS AGREEMENT (this “Agreement”), dated December 30, 2016 (the “Effective Date”), is
agreement_date.reasoning: The opening sentence of the agreement expressly states the agreement is "dated December 30, 2016" which identifies the date the agreement was made/signed.

effective_date.raw_snippet: THIS AGREEMENT (this “Agreement”), dated December 30, 2016 (the “Effective Date”), is
effective_date.reasoning: The same clause equates the date of the agreement (December 30, 2016) with the defined term "Effective Date." Additionally, Section 2.1 refers to commencement on the Effective Date, confirming its role as the effective date.

expiration_date.raw_snippet: This Agreement shall commence on the Effective Date and shall be valid until the [* * *] (the “Initial Term”).
expiration_date.reasoning: Section 2.1 defines the Initial Term but the actual duration/expiration is redacted (marked [* * *]) so the explicit expiration term cannot be determined from the text.

governing_law.raw_snippet:
This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the substantive Laws of the [* * *], excluding any rules of conflicts of
laws that would apply the substantive laws of any other jurisdiction.
governing_law.reasoning: Clause 1.6 (Applicable Law) is the governing law clause, but the jurisdiction is redacted ([* * *]) so the governing jurisdiction cannot be determined from the document.

notice_period.raw_snippet:
a) Customer delivers written notice of termination to Supplier at least [* * *] prior to the expiration date of the Initial Term, which termination shall
be effective as of the expiration date of the Initial Term;
notice_period.reasoning: Section 18.1(a) sets the advance written notice requirement to terminate prior to the expiration of the Initial Term (i.e., the notice needed to prevent renewal). That period is redacted ([* * *]), so the specific notice period cannot be extracted.

renewal_term.raw_snippet: Should the Parties have not agreed to the following agreement by [* * *], this Agreement shall automatically stay in force for a maximum of [* * *] (unless otherwise mutually agreed by the Parties or as otherwise set forth in Section 18.1(a)) or until the Parties have signed the follow-on agreement (the “Renewal Term”).
renewal_term.reasoning: Section 2.1 explains that if the parties have not agreed to a subsequent long-term agreement by a specified (redacted) date, the Agreement will automatically remain in force for a maximum (redacted) period (the Renewal Term) or until a follow-on agreement is signed. The actual renewal duration and the cutoff date are redacted, so the renewal term cannot be normalized.
